<br>
I guess I had higher hopes for this server. The constant bickering has grown quite repulsive. The general lack of intelligence conveyed in most of these flames only serves to add confusion to whichever topic has actually been put forth. Nothing seems to be resolved, and the battles continue to go back and forth until the post is eventually locked or deleted, or disappears into obscurity.<br>
<br>
I have read articulate, intelligent posts form several members of F&amp;F; Bako, Gore, Heagan, etc. I cannot say the same for many of those who have spoken against them recently, save Tiesto. Frankly, these flames have come across as simple whining. If there was an honest point to be made, it has been buried beneath the attacks and insults.<br>
<br>
I am not an advocate of F&amp;F. I have only rarely seen them in game. Those encounters have gone well enough. It will be a long time before I bother attaining the levels they have, and so, little of what they do has much effect on my characters career just yet.<br>
<br>
However, I can learn from them. They have been to places I haven't, and accomplished things I wish to accomplish in the future. I would like to see them continue posting, and sharing their knowledge and experiences, without reprisal from the many who feel it neccessary to attack anything they say.<br>
<br>
Nor am I now, nor will I ever be, a member of Starspun. This is also a good guild, with very nice people. I do not hold it against them for defending their friends in F&amp;F, as any friend would. Nor would I blame them for defending them were they not allied in some ways. The attacks have been base and rude, and deserved defense, from whomever.<br>
<br>
Please discontinue these flames. They serve no purpose. <br>
<br>
I know this is a free board. I acknowledge we will not always get along. Yet, to be blunt, I came to Fvie to get away from this bullshit. If my only recourse to avoid such is to leave, then I feel I must do so. I am sorry it has come to this. I had hoped for more. Good luck, all of you, on Fvie.<br>
<br>
Vallaelanan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belika>Belika</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/01 1:21:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re</span><hr size=1> Vallaelanan,<br>
<br>
Firiona Vie is still an excellent server, with its low population it feels more like a small little village if you will.<br>
<br>
There really aren't that many people so when stuff is flying around it is easy to absorb and obtain cause news carries easier.<br>
<br>
Don't take it the wrong way, but if you don't read the Soapbox flames, and stick to The Story Telling Threads, and RP threads and all around play in game you would be oblivious to the things here.<br>
<br>
Most of you don't believe it, but i'd prolly really never beat bako down with my coat hanger, if you haven't figured it out already most the time we post is 5 in the morning right before we go to bed.<br>
<br>
No points ever come across in flames and I apologize if I have turned you from this server, or if anyone else has.<br>
<br>
I can promise you there are ton of good guilds on the server, Fire and Fury included once you reach appropriate level.<br>
<br>
